data.content:
Chương I: Khái Quát Chung Về Bảo Hiểm
This chapter provides a general overview of insurance, covering risk management strategies and their classifications.

Tự bảo hiểm
Self-insurance refers to individuals or organizations setting aside funds to cover potential losses, with limitations in scale and capital accumulation.

Chuyển nhượng rủi ro
This method transfers risk by distributing losses among a group, often through insurance, with advantages and limitations regarding pooling capacity.

Chấp nhận rủi ro
This method involves self-insurance, where individuals or organizations absorb the consequences of risk using their own resources.

Rủi ro
Risk is defined as an unpredictable hazard that can lead to loss, and is the central concept addressed in the text.

Lắp camera chống trộm
This is an example of a preventive measure to reduce the probability of risk occurrence.

Đội mũ bảo hiểm
This is an example of a measure to reduce the consequences of risk, specifically for personal injury.

Hệ thống chữa cháy
This is an example of a measure to minimize the consequences of risk, specifically for fire-related losses.

Bảo hiểm
Insurance is the core subject of the study material, encompassing risk management, prevention, and transfer mechanisms.

Discarded Content
Discarded Content refers to unused or outdated material, such as text fragments or drafts, that can be analyzed, reframed, or repurposed for new use.

Assistant
The Assistant is an entity capable of analyzing, reframing, or repurposing discarded content to assist users in deriving value from unused material.

University of Foreign Trade
The University of Foreign Trade is the academic institution referenced in the document as the current institution of the student.

Vietnam Socialist Republic
The Vietnam Socialist Republic is the sovereign state where the document is issued, symbolizing the national context of the academic transfer request.

Hanoi
Hanoi is the city where the document is signed, indicating the administrative location of the institution.

Student Transfer Request Form
The Student Transfer Request Form is a formal document used to request a change of academic institution, including personal details and reasons for transfer.

Transfer Request
The transfer request is a formal academic action to move from one educational institution to another, including justification and completion of obligations.

Student
The student is the individual submitting the form, providing personal information and requesting to transfer to another institution.

Faculty/Department
The Faculty or Department is a sub-unit of the University of Foreign Trade, responsible for managing student affairs and academic programs.

Student ID
The student ID is a unique identifier assigned to the student, used for administrative and academic record-keeping purposes.

Credit Hours Accumulated
The total number of credit hours the student has completed, used to assess academic progress and eligibility for transfer.

GPA
The student’s GPA (Grade Point Average) is a measure of academic performance, indicated in the form as a numerical value out of 4.0.

Signature
The signature is the formal acknowledgment by the student, indicating agreement to the terms of the transfer request.

Date of Submission
The date of submission is recorded at the end of the form, indicating when the request was formally submitted.
